14
October
UBA Ghana MD/CEO Calls for the Removal of Trade Barriers in West Africa

Addressing the participants at the opening ceremony of the just ended Ghana- Togo -Benin - Nigeria Business summit, Mr Gabriel Edgal stated that “it is much easier to transfer funds from Togo, Benin or Ghana to Europe and the United States than it is to transfer funds between the four COPAZ countries.   As a consequence, he continued “the amount of funds that are physically transferred across the borders as a cannot be fathomed. The many physical barriers, i am afraid are rather encouraging money laundering across the borders which is a huge loss to the formal banking sector and revenue lost to government”. He emphasized.

He further mentioned that due to the seemingly inconvertible nature of the local currencies, payments for goods and services are made in foreign currency thus putting undue pressure on a country’s reserves. “This should not be acceptable” he insisted.  “We must encourage convertibility amongst our currencies if we are to achieve any form of financial integration” he added.

Mr Edgal in conclusion opined that “Banks must create the settlement platform for trade across our borders by facilitating settlement in local currency between all market participants, customers and banks thus reducing the huge requirement for foreign exchange”.

The summit which served as an arena for networking for partnerships and learning about the various opportunities in the four countries both as individual nations and as one contiguous bloc for business was organized by Vintage Visions with UBA as the lead sponsor.
 

16
September
UBA (Ghana) Limited Meets New Capital Requirement

In line with the UBA Group’s proactive nature, the Bank embarked upon a rights issue, which has been successfully completed. The entire deposit for shares received, has significantly raised shareholders funds to over GHC60 million as required by the Bank of Ghana.

The Bank of Ghana set the end of December 2009 for all foreign owned commercial banks in Ghana to have a minimum capitalization of GHC60 million to be able to operate on a universal banking license while indigenous banks have up to 2012 to meet this new capital requirement.

UBA (Ghana) Limited is a subsidiary of the United Bank for Africa PLC which is one of Africa’s leading financial institutions offering services to more than 7 million customers from 750 branches through about 15,000 employees and over 2000 ATMs in 19 countries.

With presence in New York, London and Paris, UBA is connecting people and businesses across Africa through retail and wholesale banking, innovative cross-border payments and collections, trade finance, investment banking and a state of the art electronic banking platform.

UBA (Ghana) commenced operations nearly five years ago with its revolutionary Cashless Account which for the first time brought banking to the door step of all Ghanaians. Already, UBA (Ghana) has a footprint of 26-networked branches, and 40 ATMS (VISA enabled) and over 500 employees spread across Accra, Tema, Kumasi, Takoradi and Aflao.

UBA (Ghana) was recently awarded the Best Bank in Customer Service which is a testament to the Bank’s avowed commitment to provide Customer Centric banking solutions to the Ghanaian public.
 

07
September
The UBA Double Triple Savings Promo

United Bank for Africa (Ghana) Limited has launched a Mega Savings Promo dubbed the UBA DOUBLE TRIPLE SAVINGS PROMO.

The Double Triple Promo doubles the interest on two months savings and triples the interest on three months savings with UBA. The Double Triple Promo is designed to create excitement for the bank’s products whilst stimulating customer interest in doing business with UBA and rewarding existing customers for choosing UBA. 
 

Target Market.

Customers and non-customers of the bank – Individual Savings Account holders including sole proprietors

How it works

•    New customer opens  a Savings account with UBA

•    Deposits a minimum of GHC100 in the Double Triple Savings account

•    Existing customers top up their accounts with a minimum GHC100 to participate in the promo. However, Double or Triple interest will be paid only on the incremental deposit.

•    Save funds for 60 or 90 days without any withdrawals.

•    Existing balance before Promo will earn normal interest rate of 5%

•    The new savings will earn Double or Triple the normal interest if not touched for 60 or 90 days respectively.

•    The account will automatically be credited with the interest after the 60 or 90-day anniversary depending on the option chosen by the customer.

 

Conditions

•    Any withdrawal from the account during the Promo will result in the loss of the triple or double interest. The account will revert to a normal account earning 5% interest.

•    However if a customer reverts to the normal account but tops up beyond his closing balance as of September 1 he still qualifies to earn double or triple interest on his incremental deposit if  there is no withdrawal for 60 or 90 days..

 

According to the Executive Director of UBA, Mr. Daniel Addo, the UBA Double Triple Savings Promo will help encourage a savings culture among UBA customers and the public.  
 

Duration

The Promo lasts from September 1 till November 30, 2009.

31
July
UBA Wins Financial Excellence Award

UBA Ghana (Limited) has been presented with an award at the just ended Ashanti Financial Services Excellence Awards last night for its immense contribution to the economic development of Ashanti.

The award ceremony organized under the auspices and blessing of the Asantehene His Majesty Otumfuo Osei Tutu II was well attended by Kingmakers, business men and women, policy makers and financial institutions nationwide.


The Ashanti Financial Services Excellence Awards scheme was instituted under the auspices of Manhyia Palace in 2004 with the objective of acknowledging the vital contribution of financial service providers to the development of Ashanti.

This year’s award is very significant since it takes account of the performance of financial institutions during the 10 year reign of the Asantehene, Otumfou Osei Tutu II

Overall, UBA was acknowledged for its unrivalled bouquet of innovative and customer centric products.

The award was received on behalf of UBA by Chris Odamtten (Regional Director, Retail and Consumer Banking 3), Rosemond Adjei (Relationship Officer, Adum branch) and Daniel Lawson (Branch Manager, Adum branch).
 

22
June
UBA Reaffirms Commitment to SMEs Growth in Africa.

The Management of the United Bank for Africa (UBA) Plc, Africa’s global bank has restated its commitment to the growth and development of Small and Medium Scale Enterprises (SME’s) in Africa, with a view to stimulating and deepening the economy of the continent.

This was disclosed in Accra Ghana, by the Managing Director/CEO, UBA Ghana Limited, Mr. Gabriel Edgal at the opening ceremony of the UBA Growing Businesses/EMPRETEC Workshop for SMEs in Ghana, holding at the La Palm Royal Beach Resort from Monday June 22 – Saturday, June 27, 2009.

Edgal said that the workshop for Small and Medium Scale Enterprises (SMEs) in Ghana is most appropriate at this time when the Government of Ghana has committed to push for Economic Empowerment, Employment Generation, Poverty Alleviation and Food Security among others.

He said that UBA believes in the critical role SME’s play as a catalyst for economic revival and growth hence, the bank have planned the workshop to run in Nigeria, Ghana, Cameroon, Cote D Ivoire, Burkina Faso and Uganda.

“We are embarking on this huge project because statistics have shown that a size able percentage of all businesses in Africa fall under the SME category and contribute approximately 40 percent of GDP of most African countries. With UBA fast establishing presence across Africa and with presence in 19 African countries already, it is our ambition to roll out this workshop in all the African countries” he said.

Commenting on UBA’s foray into the SME sector in Africa, Edgal noted that the bank was the first post consolidated bank in Nigeria to launch a N50 billion naira agro support fund farmers (especially small scale farmers) towards achieving food security in Nigeria.

He said that at the end of the workshop, participants are expected to identify SME businesses having acquired requisite tools and business skills to enable them develop their businesses, generate employment and create wealth for Africans.

While declaring the workshop open, Hon. John Gywtuah (MP), Ghana’s Deputy Minister of Trade and Industry commended UBA plc for being steadfast with its promise to help in the development of African businesses especially in Ghana where it has planed SME workshops in Accra and Kumasi.

He said that the gesture by UBA EMPRETEC will go along way in ensuring that knowledge acquired by participants at the workshop will be translated into improved and technically sound businesses endeavors in Ghana in particular and Africa as a whole.

In her opening remark, Chief Executive Officer, EMPRETEC Africa Foundation, Mrs. Onari Duke said that the workshop is created as platform by UBA Growing Businesses in partnership with EMPRETEC Africa Foundation for supporting the growth of SMEs across Africa in the area of capacity and entrepreneurial development.


She listed areas of focus during the workshop to include; skills enhancement & development, attitudinal training, access to finance and creation of businesses networking opportunities.
 

11
May
UBA Ghana Wins Laurel at 8th Ghana Banking Awards

At the 8th Ghana Banking Awards ceremony held at the Accra International Conference Centre over the weekend, UBA won the award for Best Customer Care. This award was presented to the bank with the most satisfied customers for the year under review as the banks were assessed based on factors including friendliness, professionalism and efficiency in dealing with customers, convenience of access to services and quick attention and response to enquiries. The bank was also the second runner up in the product innovation category.

The annual Ghana Banking Awards seeks to engender keen competition among banks operat­ing in the country and ultimately improve the quality and efficiency of financial services delivery to Ghana’s banking population.

 

 

11
May
UBA Ghana Introduces DREAM N DRIVE Promotion

In our unrelenting efforts to make it easier for salaried workers to acquire brand new vehicles of their choice, United Bank for Africa (UBA) Ghana’s Best Bank in Customer Care and second best in Product Innovation in partnership with SIC, the Honda Place, Audi and Skoda centers is introducing the “UBA Dream N Drive” Promotion.

The “UBA Dream N Drive” Promotion is an automobile purchase scheme aimed at supporting salaried workers across the country to purchase and own cars of their dreams with a deposit of 10%. The promotion also offers customers one year discounted comprehensive insurance cover on vehicles purchased from SIC.

The promotion starts from May 11 to July 30, 2009.

The cars on offer in the promotion are various models, saloon cars of Honda, Audi, and Skoda available at their respective showrooms on the Graphic Road and close to the Obetsebi Lamptey Circle, Abossey Okai - Kaneshie.

About Partners:

UBA Ghana, a subsidiary of UBA Plc has its value propositions geared towards identifying customer needs and expectations and providing value adding solutions for those needs. The overriding goal is to be at the forefront of banking innovation, defining the industry landscape and creating value for all our stakeholders, thereby positioning us as a “role model for African Businesses”.

The Bank has developed a branch foot-print and delivery network that has ensured that the Bank’s services are always within reach of valued customers.

UBA Ghana currently has a footprint of 24 fully networked branches in Accra, Tema, Kumasi, Takoradi and Aflao.

The Honda Place Gh. Ltd & Audi Centre, for the past decade has expanded rapidly into West Africa’s largest business conglomerates with well consolidated business lines, robust infrastructure and valuable human resources.

SIC, the pacesetters in insurance in the country has over 100 offices nationwide and offers superior and quality insurance services. In times of insurance needs, do not hesitate to talk to the Professionals in insurance at any of their insurance Halls.


 

23
April
UBA Ghana Bids Nnamdi Okonkwo Farewell

At a farwell cocktail party organized for the outgoing MD/CEO of UBA Ghana, Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo, the board chairman, Mr Kwame Pianim paid glowing tributes to the outgoing MD/CEO for his outstanding performance and immense contribution to the success of the bank.

He described him as a true leader who distinguished himself creditably, and as someone who does not compromise mediocrity. In a short response, Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo, who has eighteen years banking exprience under his belt, described his stay in Ghana as one of the challenging and interesting in the discharge of his duties. The outgoing MD thanked his colleagues for their collaboration in working hand -in -hand with him,and ensuring the growth of the bank.

The new MD/CEO, Mr Edgal Gabriel commended Nnamdi Okonkwo for the good job done and promised to ensure continuity of what he (Mr Okonkwo) left behind. Mr Edgal Gabriel also called on his colleagues to give him the same support enjoyed by the outgoing MD to ensure continuous growth of the bank.

27
March
UBA Ghana Opens Eight (8) New Branches

As part of UBA’s efforts in sending banking services to the doorsteps of its customers, the bank recently officially opened 8 new branches in Kumasi in the Ashanti region on Thursday 19th March 2009.
The launch of the new branches was part of a programme to inaugurate eight (8) branches bringing the total number of branches to twenty – four nationwide. The new branches include:
 

  • Accra/Tema (Greater Accra Region)
  • Kantamanto
  • Abeka Lapaz
  • Tema Comm.4
  • Kumasi (Ashanti Region)
  • Alaba
  • Suame
  • Kejetia
  • KNUST
  • Takoradi (Western Region)
  • Kokompe

    In his address, Nnamdi Okonkwo MD/CEO of UBA Ghana said “the rapid branch roll-out strategy of the bank attest to the fact that UBA Ghana has full confidence in the Ghanaian economy and that the strategy is also in line with the bold mandate we have set ourselves to democratize banking in Ghana, by making banking products and services widely and easily available to all Ghanaians irrespective of their socio-economic circumstances and geographical location”. In expressing his gratitude to the Board and management of the bank, the Akyempenhene, Oheneba Nana Adusei poku who represented the king of Ashanti, Otumfuo Osei Tutu ll, observed that it is very encouraging and in place to commend the way and manner management of the bank has steered the affairs of the bank to expand within this short period. Board Chairman, Mr Kwame Pianim stressed the bank’s commitment to provide quality banking service to the people of the country. He added that the bank had adopted new and flexible banking services to enable entrepreneurs, students, traders and artisans to interact with the bank. On behalf of the board and management of UBA Ghana, Nnamdi Okonkwo MD/CEO donated of a double –cabin Nissan Pick-up to the Kwame Nkrumah University of science and Technology for use by the University security department.
